snippet.textDisplay:
Be Strong Brie and Bryan it's not easy but you will overcome.
We lost a dog like 20 yrs ago. His name was Lexie. He was the best. Took care of me when I was little. He was a friend and a family to all. But one day Lexie left and never came back. Searched for him but couldn't find him. Years have passed with the hope of seeing Lexie again until we gave up 😢. It Hurts even today. We don't know whether Lexie is alive or not. But hopes that wherever he is, he's happy.......I came up with this poem after we gave up on ever seeing Lexie again and everyone has a copy of it and a photo of Lexie in their house * ******
🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹
"Lexie, you were a part of us, you bonded us together as a family,
Each day with you was special and unique...
Whenever we had a bad day at work or school,
You knew how to bring a smile back to our faces....
With you, there was no a dull moment..
Your giggles and your kindness were special....
You had respect for everyone and very obedient.....

Lexie, you were a friend and a comforter, your companionship was all that we needed..
You completed our family,
You held us together...

But then, a day came and you left,
We came back from our daily routines and couldn't find you...
We thought you went to play as usual but you never showed up....
Lexie we searched everywhere for you,
We walked miles and miles looking for you,
What happened? Did any of us annoy you?
Why did you leave without a goodbye?
Thinking about you brings tears,
A moment without you, is torture,
You didn't teach us how to live without you...
Without you, life has never been the same... You're irreplaceable!
Wherever you are, we still love you..
In our hearts and memories, we will always love you and Cherish you.
Love from the Lexies Family. ❤️❤️🌹. (we miss you come back to us if possible)

After Lexies' disappearance, it was hard for us to get another dog. 😢
